'''Kuut''' (Kuut: Cèn Bèrom ''ku'' Berom) ja yet a̱lyem á̱ lyiat a̱ swak mi̱ [[Si̱tet Pi̱lato]] ma̱ a̱byin [[Naijeriya]]. The language is locally numerically important and is consistently spoken by [[Berom people|Berom]] of all ages in rural areas. However, the Berom are shifting to [[Hausa language|Hausa]] in cities.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.ethnologue.com/18/language/bom/|title=Berom|work=Ethnologue|access-date=2017-07-24}}</ref> The small Cen and [[Nincut language|Nincut]] dialects may be separate languages. Approximately 1 million (2010) people speak in this language.<ref name=":0" />

Berom is spoken in a large area just to the south of [[Jos, Nigeria|Jos]] city in [[Plateau State]], Nigeria.<ref name="Blench2021"/>

